result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kelly A Nerge appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Larry R Pruden in court for Kelly A Nerge.  Prosecuting attorney Vivien L. TenHaken in court for the State of Wisconsin. Minutes filed.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for November 8, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
Cash bond filed. Defendant refused to sign.

BOND TO COVER 22CF568, 21CF633 & 21CF556

NO UNSUPERVISED CONTACT WITH MINORS. Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol. Defendant shall not possess or use illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.  Defendant will not possess any firearms, ammunition or other weapons.  Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any victim(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  VICTIM(S)/RESIDENCE(S): NO CONTACT WITH A.D., L.R.J. dob 9-13-2006 or RESIDENCE, L.J.J. dob 4-27-2010 or RESIDENCE.  Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.

Called at 1:23 PM. Defendant Kelly A Nerge in court, in custody by video. Samuel Berg appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Josh Ryan appeared for bond purposes only, defendant qualifies for SPD. Discussion as to bond. State asks that prior bond forfeited. Argument by Attorney Ryan. State recites prior convictions. Total $10,000 cash bond set. Minutes filed.
Hearing scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
